Package: pepitope
Title: Extract the peptide context around mutations in a VCF
Version: 0.2.914
Authors@R: c(
    person('Michael', 'Schubert', email='mschu.dev@gmail.com',
           role = c('aut', 'cre'),
           comment = c(ORCID='0000-0002-6862-5221'))
    )
Maintainer: Michael Schubert <mschu.dev@gmail.com>
Description: Given a reference genome and VCF file, this package will provide
    the upstream/downstream peptide context of a variant. It will generate a
    summary report for protein-coding variants including the reference and
    mutated allele, read coverage, amino acid sequence, and other information.
    It can also be used to remove restriction sites from cDNA, alongside other
    helper functions.
URL: https://github.com/mschubert/pepitope
BugReports: https://github.com/mschubert/pepitope/issues
